    • Method Detail

      • getContent

        public List<Serializable> getContent()
        The sql-query element declares a named SQL query string Gets the value of the content property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the content property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getContent().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<JaxbHbmNativeQueryReturnType> String JAXBElement<JaxbHbmNativeQueryCollectionLoadReturnType> JAXBElement<JaxbHbmNativeQueryScalarReturnType> JAXBElement<JaxbHbmNativeQueryJoinReturnType> JAXBElement<JaxbHbmSynchronizeType> JAXBElement<JaxbHbmQueryParamType>
